{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.14",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 14 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:1",
      "text": "“Man, who is born of a woman, is of few days, and full of trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:2",
      "text": "He grows up like a flower, and is cut down. He also flees like a shadow, and doesn’t continue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:3",
      "text": "Do you open your eyes on such a one, and bring me into judgment with you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:4",
      "text": "Who can bring a clean thing out of an unclean? Not one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:5",
      "text": "Seeing his days are determined, the number of his months is with you, and you have appointed his bounds that he can’t pass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:6",
      "text": "Look away from him, that he may rest, until he accomplishes, as a hireling, his day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:7",
      "text": "“For there is hope for a tree if it is cut down, that it will sprout again, that the tender branch of it will not cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:8",
      "text": "Though its root grows old in the earth, and its stock dies in the ground,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:9",
      "text": "yet through the scent of water it will bud, and sprout boughs like a plant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:10",
      "text": "But man dies, and is laid low. Yes, man gives up the spirit, and where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:11",
      "text": "As the waters fail from the sea, and the river wastes and dries up,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:12",
      "text": "so man lies down and doesn’t rise. Until the heavens are no more, they will not awake, nor be roused out of their sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:13",
      "text": "“Oh that you would hide me in Sheol, that you would keep me secret until your wrath is past, that you would appoint me a set time and remember me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:14",
      "text": "If a man dies, will he live again? I would wait all the days of my warfare, until my release should come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:15",
      "text": "You would call, and I would answer you. You would have a desire for the work of your hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:16",
      "text": "But now you count my steps. Don’t you watch over my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:17",
      "text": "My disobedience is sealed up in a bag. You fasten up my iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:18",
      "text": "“But the mountain falling comes to nothing. The rock is removed out of its place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:19",
      "text": "The waters wear the stones. The torrents of it wash away the dust of the earth. So you destroy the hope of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:20",
      "text": "You forever prevail against him, and he departs. You change his face, and send him away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:21",
      "text": "His sons come to honor, and he doesn’t know it. They are brought low, but he doesn’t perceive it of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.14.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:22",
      "text": "But his flesh on him has pain, and his soul within him mourns.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
